#####
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE -- READ IT OR DEAL WITH IT NOT WORKING.
# 
# 1. Leave the variable names alone!
# 2. See #1.
# 3. Again, leave them alone.  Failure to follow this will break Newcall.
# 4. The defaults are shown below.  If you want to change these, change the color
#    code, not the variable.
#    You can visit the following site for color options and codes:
#    https://misc.flogisoft.com/bash/tip_colors_and_formatting
#    For example:
#    If you want to change headers (default is yellow) to blue, change the "HEAD"
#    entry below and it'll change.
#####

### COLORS ###

# Alerts - Default is Bold Red.
ALERT=$(echo -en '\033[01;31m')

# Cool! - Default is Bold Green
COOL=$(echo -en '\033[01;32m')

# Headers - Default is Bold Yellow
HEAD=$(echo -en '\033[01;33m')

# Informational Messages - Default is Bold Light Blue.
INFO=$(echo -en '\033[01;94m')

# Highlight Option 1 - Default is Bold Cyan
HIL1=$(echo -en '\033[01;36m')

# Highlight Option 2 - Default is Bold Magenta
HIL2=$(echo -en '\033[01;35m')

# White Text - Sets the text color to white.
WHT=$(echo -en '\033[01;37m')

# Title Section - Default is Blue background with White text.
TITLE=$(echo -en '\033[44m')

# Underline Text - Simply Underlines the text.
ULNE=$(echo -en '\033[4m')